 MODE (mohd) n. A general state, usually used with an adjective describing
the state. "No time to hack; I'm in thesis mode." Usage: in its jargon sense,
MODE is most often said of people, though it is sometimes applied to programs
and inanimate objects. "If you're on a TTY, E will switch to non-display
mode." In particular, see HACK MODE, DAY MODE, NIGHT MODE, and YOYO MODE;
also COM MODE, TALK MODE, and GABRIEL MODE.